    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n8247" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῥῑγέω</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ϝρῖγος</span>), fut. inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῥῑγήσειν</span>, aor. (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐρ</span>)<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ρί̄γησα</span>, perf., w.
          pres. signif., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔρρῑγα</span>, subj. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐρρί̄γῃσι</span>, plup. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐρρί̄γει</span>: properly, to shudder with cold, but in Homer
          always met., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">shudder</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">at</span>) with fear,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">be horrified</span>, abs., also w. acc., inf., <i><span class="en">Il. 3.353</span></i>; part., <i><span class="en">Il. 4.279</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; μή</span>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            23.216</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
